      "content": "Feeling heavy in your chest and short of breath during light activities could indicate that your asthma isn't well-controlled, and it's important not to self-adjust your medication without professional guidance. Over-reliance on a rescue inhaler like salbutamol can lead to worsening asthma control and potential side effects. I strongly advise you to consult your healthcare provider for a proper evaluation and adjustment of your treatment plan. Your health is paramount, and professional advice is crucial in managing your condition effectively.",
